<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="500" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,505,818]" pageId="5" pageNumber="500">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,649,674]" pageId="5" pageNumber="500">Remarks.</emphasis>
In the description, the term “pharyngeal knobs” has been used to denote the pharyngeal pores. This may cause confusion as the term pharyngeal knobs has also been used for the drumstick-like sensorial organs present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Remane" authorityYear="1927" box="[266,567,721,746]" class="Gastrotricha (awaiting allocation)" family="Cephalodasyidae" genus="Pleurodasys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macrodasyida" pageId="5" pageNumber="500" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="helgolandicus">
<emphasis box="[266,567,721,746]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="500">Pleurodasys helgolandicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Furthermore, nomenclature and functional role of the accessory reproductive organs as indicated in the original description should be revised in light of the recent literature (e.g., Kieneke &amp; Schmidt-Rhaesa 2015).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
